<h2 class="bold font-l">Friendship is Magic</h2>
<p class="_pmvv-vidbox-descTxt">
While inside Starlight Glimmer's nightmare, Princess Celestia is introduced to her hypothetical Super-Powered Evil Side: Daybreaker. Where as Princess Luna transformed into Nightmre Moon out of jealousy and bitterness towards her older sister, Daybreaker stemmed from Princess Celestia embracing her selfishness and stopped caring for anyone, potentially turning herself into a tyrannical ruler. This alone terrifies Celestia, and swears that she will never become her. </p>
</div>
<div class="video-examples-thumbs">
<a href="#video-link" data-video-id="dwydws" data-video-descrip="Regime Superman turned to dictatorial tactics because he thought it was the only way to keep the world safe, but after killing Luthor, his selfish side shows, unleashing his military and Doomsday on Metropolis and Gotham for daring to question him and planning to kill the main universe's Superman and take his Lois, regardless of what she may think. After realizing just how much of an insane monster his Regime counterpart has become, this leaves multiverse Supes spooked, wondering if he'll end up like his Regime counterpart." data-video-title="Injustice: Gods Among Us" data-video-url="https://d1w6li7s85ibls.cloudfront.net/qvbr/dwydws_640x360p_qvbr.mp4" data-video-thumbnail="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/dwydws.jpg" data-video-trope="Main/EvilMeScaresMe" data-video-tropename="Evil Me Scares Me" data-video-approval="APPROVED" data-video-troper-rating="" data-video-average-rating="" data-video-rating-count="" data-video-media-sources="VideoGame/InjusticeGodsAmongUs" class="video-launch-link video-overlay-link video-background-image lazy-image" data-src="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/dwydws.jpg">
<p><span class="bold">Injustice: Gods...</span></p>
</a>
</div>
</div>
</div>
